    <section id="id1171490061934">
      <title>Assessment</title>
      <para id="id1171498465972"><emphasis><emphasis effect="italics">Learning Outcome 1:</emphasis></emphasis>The learner will be able to recognise, describe and represent numbers and their relationships, and to count, estimate, calculate and check with competence and confidence in solving problems.</para>
      <para id="id1171492561128"><emphasis><emphasis effect="italics">Assessment Standard 1.1:</emphasis></emphasis> We know this when the learner counts to at least 34 everyday objects reliably;</para>
      <para id="id4622507"><emphasis><emphasis effect="italics">Assessment Standard 1.4:</emphasis></emphasis> We know this when the learner orders, describes and compares whole numbers to at least 2-digit numbers.</para>
    </section>
